genresAdvancedInfo.name: swahili gospel
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre of gospel music originating from East Africa, characterized by its fusion of traditional African rhythms with Christian lyrics. The genre has gained popularity worldwide and is often used in church services and Christian gatherings. The lyrics are usually in Swahili, a widely spoken language in East Africa, and often address themes of faith, hope, and salvation.
